Birds are one of my biggest fears! Especially because I can't see them and they are unpredictable, I have a total fight-or-flight reaction to them that I can't control-- I thought I was going for a relaxing swim and did not expect to be surrounded by birds!! But it's still really important to face your fears no matter what they might be or how big or small they may seem. Every little bit counts!¬†Never forget to tell yourself #yesIcan

I don't know about you but my mood 100% changes depending on the weather and honestly, it's a real pain. Living somewhere that is mainly sunny has made it a lot easier , but if its rainy rainy , or the sun isnt out that day , or it starts to get a bit cold, my mood is really affected. It's been that way since I lost my vision 11 years ago since my brain cant register daylight or light in general quite the same as others. Not all blind people face this, and many sighted people do face it, but my vision loss definitely triggered it in my specific case. All this is to say, that the Miami sunshine is doing me good right now! And for those struggling and missing your warm sunshine, run a hot bath, drink some warm tea, snuggle up with a hot water bottle in bed, and read a good book. The sun will rise again! XO .
